dosbox: A x86 emulator with Tandy/Herc/CGA/EGA/VGA/SVGA graphics, sound and DOS
dosbox:
dosbox: DOSBox is a x86 emulator with Tandy/Hercules/CGA/EGA/VGA/SVGA graphics, 
dosbox: sound and DOS. It's been designed to run old DOS games under 
dosbox: platforms that don't support it. (Win2k/XP/FreeBSD/Linux/MAC OS X) 
dosbox: The following legacy sound devices are emulated: PC Speaker, Creative 
dosbox: CMS/Gameblaster, Tandy 3 voice, Adlib, Sound Blaster Pro/16, Disney 
dosbox: Soundsource and a Gravis Ultrasound. MPU-401 is forwarded to the host. 
